comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-09T21:35:58.168Z",codex-foundation,Specialized agent started scoped production audit on 2026-07-09; pm-cli source and telemetry/observability configuration are out of scope.
  "2026-07-09T21:36:07.865Z",codex-foundation,"2026-07-09 scope checkpoint: inventorying GitHub reports, current PR branch, dependency versions, release automation, package activation, real-workspace behavior, and full-history privacy posture before implementation."
  "2026-07-11T19:39:43.891Z",codex-foundation,"Verified release:check; 37/37 opted-in real-data tests passed against pm-brief and pm-context; pm-changelog release:check also passed. GitHub Dependabot and secret-scanning open alerts: 0; code-scanning is not configured. Full patch scan found only CI secret references,never values. Historical commit metadata contains the repository owner email but no credentials or hosted-service/user data."
  "2026-07-11T19:57:14.249Z",codex-foundation,"PR #10 review round 1: implemented Sourcery offline-mode regression coverage and consistent audit-unavailable diagnostics; implemented Gemini structured npm audit error parsing. Local Greptile previously 5/5."
  "2026-07-11T20:06:19.617Z",codex-foundation,"PR #10 review round 2: addressed Gemini Windows PATH delimiter and .cmd mock findings,string-shaped npm audit errors,and Sourcery duplication concerns by centralizing audit gating/diagnostics and test-bin creation."
  "2026-07-11T20:16:10.812Z",codex-foundation,"PR #10 review round 3: hardened unknown audit error serialization per Sourcery. Retained black-box assertions on the user-facing diagnostic prefix rather than exporting an internal implementation constant solely for tests."
  "2026-07-11T20:43:23.745Z",codex-foundation,"PR #10 final thread pass: rendered scan diagnostics in markdown per Greptile P1; added stderr-only/non-JSON audit regression; enriched spawn errors; narrowed unknown-object diagnostics to code/summary/message to avoid sensitive payload serialization."
